<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100644885263646></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100644885263646><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=100644885263646>My strategy for getting out of 30.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=100644885263646#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=6400><span id=Scholar>ZomorSoulsaver</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>92 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Nov 22nd 12:07 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.32]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have found that your first hell level, 30, is quite a slow one. Not hard but just slow. My best advice for Bards in LOIO is not to group unless you suck at kiting/fear kiting/chram kiting. With the following strategy i leveled from 30-31 in about 4 hours. The best part about being in LOIO is that when you run with Selos on, you can outrace the MoBs enough so that they break off and wander off. Be careful though, they will come back if you go back towards them even if you cant see them yet.<br><br> First off, set up your song hotkeys with 1) Selos, 2) Hymn, 3) Jons Whistling Warsong, 4) Bellow, 5) Solons Song of the Sirens, 6) Selos Consonant Chain, 7) Fufil's, 8) Invis or Fear, 9) /pet attack, 10) /pet target. <br><br>Then, make sure you have your drum in hand and head towards the mill. From the mill, go to the Skeleton Ruins where the higher end MoBs are. The, facing the ruins, take a left and run up the hill till you go down into another ravine/valley. Then, take a right through the mountains onto a long stretch of flat land. Keep running straight until you see a big weird looking ruin. Inside of it lay 5 or 6 Goblins. The flat area to the left side of the ruins will be your kiting grounds.<br><br>Make sure you have about 5-8 minutes to spare to kite them. If the phone rings, do not answer it. If there is a knock on the door dont even blink. This process needs your full attention because even a small mistake and you will get hit by about 6 HIGHLY pissed off goblins.<br><br>That said, start off with drum in hand and selos for a tick, then charm the highest con goblin(warlord). Then press F8 and then press 9 on your numpad for you pet to attack that gob. The entir pack should beat the living bjesus out of the warlord until charm wears off. After you press F8, press 10 to target your pet. Then, when they rush you, either start twisting Selos, Fufil's and Bellow on him till he dies or charm him for another round. With the higher cons, you can usually have them stand up for 2 rounds, then finish it with a kite. Then, target another gobby of the pack and do the same with it. Keep doing this until you have 1 MoB left. Melee the snot out of that by either twisting Hymn,Warsong,Chains or Fear,Chains,Warsong. <br><br>After this, you should have about 5 or 6 bodies to loot, and about 1-2 blues of exp. Then, heal up if you were hit by the pack or last gobby and start doing regular charm kiting on the passing MoBs or swarm kite them/swarm charm kite them again. All in all, if you have a good hour or so, you can usually keep the pack going for about 20 mins because there is no real competition over there and MANY MoBs wander there. The spawn time on the Gobs is about 10-15 mins, so they are a steady, safe source of exp if you need to take breaks in between kills.<br><br>This strategy is very effective for many other places most notably OT, DL, IC, EW, and CC. The exp is faster because it takes less time to kill every MoB and you get full exp each time. VERY efficient. You can use this strategy until about 33 in LOIO and then apply it elsewhere.<br><br>Hope this Helps someone in hell. = )<br><br>Torfin<br>31'st note of the symphony<br>Bertoxxulous<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
