	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.43]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Charisma helps a helluva lot in keeping MoBs charmed and mezzed for longer. It also has a secondary role in getting those spells to stick.<br><br>I tried this out today at level 30 with 100 base cha and 130 cha with adds from equip. My charms lasted 1.5 ticks longer with the extra equip on than without it on. The average amount of time for my charm on blue MoBs would be 3.5 ticks while the average on blues with 130 cha as opposed to 100 was 5 ticks. Also, on blue charbone skeletons-decent MR-my charms would stick 1/2 of the time with 100 cha and 4/5 of the time with 130 cha. On mezzes the success rate with 100 cha was 1/4 of the time, while the rate with 130 cha was 3/5 of the time. I have not tried to time the mezzes cuz i do not use them that often and they seem unreliable to me.<br><br>Also, the difference to indif. merchants with +30 cha is about 3gp. That can amount up quite quickly. Just my studies, so charisma DOES have a pretty good effect even though it is really only on chamrs/mezzes. So Charisma is important from around 27-46 or so for charm Kiting Hill Giants and other lower level MoBs.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
